!!!
FOR UBUNTU USERS
Please see install_ubuntu script. It should install all prerequisites.
Tested with LUbuntu 14.04 and gcc 4.9.1
!!!

Required software

flex / bison
libgmp-dev
libntl-dev
realpath

boost 
boost-regex (with dev)
boost-graph (with-dev)


barvinok   # check path in 'barv_script' file

python
python-pip
python-dev

pip install easyprocess
pip install islpy
pip install gv

graphviz            
libgraphviz4       
libgv-python        
python-pygraphviz   
python-pydot
pip install pexpect
easy_install python-graph-core
easy_install python-graph-dot


Fix for problem:
Couldn't import dot_parser, loading of dot files will not be possible

sudo pip uninstall pyparsing
sudo pip install pyparsing==1.5.7
sudo pip install pydot



All above can be found in Ubuntu Packages

----
make all
make framework
----


Optionally
with root privileges
ln -s path_to/issf /usr/bin/issf

Usage:  see issf command


-----

py/gen.py - modifications for framework/obj/framework

To use codegen from CLOOG/barvinok set path in barv_script.
Version 0.36 of barvinok is supported.

--codegen=1

To use codegen from Omega+ set path in omegaplus_script.

--codegen=2

To use Omega Transitive Closure or newer functions set flag

--tc=0,1,2 

Optionally
Cloog
Wolfram Mathematica 6 (no required for compilation)

